              <h5>cinema scope: "The Grand Budapest Hotel"</h5>
              <p>"The Grand Budapest Hotel" further affirms its writer-director’s revitalization even as it rearticulates his fixations with mourning and ruptured relationships, as well as his palpable fascination with bygone eras. </p>
